ogy, European and intellectual history, museum studies, the history of science, popular culture, and colonial studies will welcome this book.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAnthropologyzGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 0aHumanismzGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 0aSciencezGermanyxHistoryy19th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aanthropologist, anthropological, german, europe, european, academic, scholarly, history, research, historical, tradition, humanism, humanist, scholarship, imperalism, 19th century, 1800s, time period, culture, cultural, science, scientific, knowledge, government, letters, photographs, pamphlet, police, museum, colonial, higher ed, college, university, textbook, major, empiricism, republic, fieldwork, artifacts.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022698341740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226983462423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226983462/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles